answers.body_markdown:
Condition variables don&#39;t have values. They&#39;re abstract objects you wait on and signal, and are *abstractly* associated with boolean-result expressions (predicates) involving other variables in your program that are protected by the associated mutex. So instead of:

    while (!node-&gt;cv)

you do:

    while (some_predicate(node))
        pthread_cond_wait(&amp;node-&gt;cv, &amp;node-&gt;mtx);

This has to be done with the mutex already locked.

